<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lesotho's Telecommunication Cut Off by Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Lesotho has been cut off
from the outside world following a 10-day strike by workers of
the country's telecommunications corporation, local media
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The strikers began their action 10 days ago to demand more
pay, during which they performed only part of their duties. The
strike at the weekend included complete work stoppages.
</P>
<P>
As a result, Telecommunications links with the outside world
were cut off. Power, which operates the telecommunications
exchange for international links, was switched off.
</P>
<P>
Many residents in the capital city of Maseru travelled to
nearby South African border town of Ladybrand today to make
international telephone calls. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
