<DOCNO> XIE19970826.0002 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Calls For State Enterprises to Perform Better </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo
has urged various localities to earnestly implement Jiang Zemin's
instructions on the reform and development of the State-owned
enterprises, and to greet the forthcoming 15th National Congress
of the Communist Party of China (CPC) with more economic
achievements.
</P>
<P>
Wu, a member of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central
Committee, conducted a fact-finding tour of east China's Jiangxi
Province between August 20-25.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier visited large and medium-sized state
enterprises in the cities of Nanchang, Jiujiang, Jingdezhen and
various localities. Wu acknowledged the province's achievements in
various fields.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that state-owned enterprises should accelerate
efforts to introduce structural readjustments and develop
marketable products to meet market demand.
</P>
<P>
Wu urged acquisitions and bankruptcies to extricate
money-losing enterprises from difficult situation.
</P>
<P>
He called for close attention to forming leading groups in
various enterprises, with priority placed on scientific
decision-making, democratic management and supervision by the
masses.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier called for various departments to create
favorable external environments for state-owned enterprises, and
for strict bans on the random collection of various fees and fines
in order to relieve the financial burdens of enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Wu expressed great concern for the life and well-being of
workers of the enterprises in the red and urged local authorities
to ensure minimum wage for affected workers and to promote
re-employment for redundant workers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
