<DOCNO> XIE19970826.0007 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepali Police Arrest Three Guerrillas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Nepali police have arrested
three persons on charges of possessing explosives and firearms in
a recent move against ultra-leftist guerrillas in Sunsari district
of eastern Nepal, the official RSS news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
In the raid on the house of Gita Thebe, one of the arrested,
police seized two hand grenades, 17 detonators, a bogus pistol,
some fuse wires, two sets of bullets and some important documents
concerning the guerrillas' activities, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Kiran Rai, who is said to be the main commander of the
guerrilla activities in Dharan municipality, was among the
arrested.
</P>
<P>
The movement in some mid-western districts launched by the
ultra-leftist guerrillas in February last year under the name of
"People's War" has claimed more than 90 lives including political
activists, policemen and civilians.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,600 individuals have been arrested since, official
statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Lokendra Bahadur Chand and Deputy Prime Minister
and Home Minister Bamdev Gautam both have categorized the
guerrillas as "terrorists".  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970826.0008 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Progressing Forward in Financial Reform (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chinese banker said that China will further reform and open
up its financial sector in the coming five years to build a
financial system according to the need of a market economy with
Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
The central bank will continue a moderately tight financial
policy in the coming years, while the state-owned commercial
banks learn advanced management expertise from overseas banks to
improve their internal risk control system.
</P>
<P>
More state-owned enterprises will be shaped into share-holding
companies in the coming year and efforts will be made to develop
the country's capital market steadily.
</P>
<P>
The PACAP conference was co-sponsored by the Chinese Education
Association for International Exchange and the PACAP REsearch
Center at University of Rhode Island.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 600 financial experts and industrialists attended the
four-day conference, to discuss the development and reform of the
financial and capital markets of China and other Asian and
Pacific countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
