<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SDP Seek Clarification of Kajiyama's Remarks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Japan's Social Democratic Party
(SDP) today urged the ruling Liberal Democratic Party (LDP) to
clarify Chief Cabinet Secretary Seiroku Kajiyama's remarks that
the proposed new Japan-U.S. defense guidelines would cover the
Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
Kazuo Oikawa, chairman of the SDP's Policy-Making Board, sought
the clarification at the council meeting of the tripartite ruling
camp comprising the LDP, SDP and New Party Sakigake.
</P>
<P>
Kajiyama said in a Sunday TV talk show that the new defense
guidelines would cover emergencies in the Taiwan Straits. China
strongly criticized his remarks, saying it signaled an attempt to
interfere in China's internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
The SDP has maintained that the Taiwan Straits should be
excluded from the geographical scope of the new guidelines.
</P>
<P>
Because of the SDP's opposition, a final agreement on the
review of the guidelines by the three parties is likely to be
delayed until Friday or later, party officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
