<DOCNO> XIE19970826.0011 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Swaziland to Repatriate Illegal Foreigners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 25 (Xinhua) -- The Swazi government today
ordered the arrest and repatriation of all foreigners who have
failed to register as refugees.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Home Affairs Gubuza Dlamini has directed the Swazi
police to effect the arrest order, Radio Mbabane said.
</P>
<P>
Aliens who wish to be Swazi citizens should apply through the
ministry's special board, he said, adding his ministry is not
responsible for foreign traders found in streets.
</P>
<P>
The minister was answering questions in parliament on whether
or not refugees have a legal right to apply for citizenship after
being in Swaziland for some years.
</P>
<P>
The matter was raised following recent clashes between Swazi
and foreign vendors.
</P>
<P>
Swazi traders have been complaining about their business being
in danger as a result of competition by immigrants, particularly
those from their eastern neighbor Mozambique. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
