<HEADLINE> Li Tieying Urges Greater Ethical and Cultural Progress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, August 25 (Xinhua) -- The advancement of China's
ethical and cultural progress should serve the needs of the market
economy and new situations emerging in the course of reforms and
opening up to the outside world, a senior Chinese official said
here today.
</P>
<P>
Li Tieying, state councillor and a member of the Political
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of
China, made the remark during a recent fact-finding tour of east
China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that promoting ethical and cultural progress is a
long-term task which should advance along the socialist road. He
added that efforts should be made to promote development of the
country's material construction.
</P>
<P>
Li said that emphasis should be placed on overcoming major
problems in various fields and aspects. 
</P>
