<HEADLINE> Bomb Parcel Kills at Least 4 in Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, August 25 (Xinhua) -- A bomb parcel exploded at Badeia
market here late this morning, killing four people and injuring 49
others, said a communique by Algerian Security Agency.
</P>
<P>
Another unexploded bomb was defused by security forces.
</P>
<P>
The area was sealed off by police and all shops in the area
closed.
</P>
<P>
In another development, an unknown terrorist group assassinated
nine members of two families in Bleida province, 50 kilometers
from Algiers, and kidnaped eight women Sunday, according to well
informed sources.
</P>
<P>
As the local legislative elections approaching, which are
scheduled on October 23, the situation is growing more and more
tense in the country.
</P>
<P>
About 800 people have been killed by terrorists in Algeria
since the general legislative elections in last July.
</P>
<P>
The army canceled a parliamentary vote in January 1992, in
which the Muslim fundamentalists might win. Since then, the
Islamic insurgents have been fighting to overthrow the current
government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
