<HEADLINE> Red Locusts Threaten Various Parts of Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 25 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzanian Ministry of
Agriculture and Cooperatives today asked for 400 million
shillings (634,000 U.S. Dollars) from the treasury for the spray
of red locusts in various parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Minister of Agriculture Njelu Kasaka said here that the
locusts are threatening plants at Malagarasi in Kigoma, Lake
Rukwa valley in Rukwa, Wembere area between Tobara and Singadi
regions and Bahi in Dodoma.
</P>
<P>
The latest outbreak of red locusts was reported at Bahi and
experts from the ministry have been sent there to survey the
situation, Kasaka said.
</P>
<P>
The money will be spent in paying for the spray of
insecticides to be done by the Addis Ababa-based Desert Locust
Control Organization -- East Africa.
</P>
<P>
The last spray on swarms of locusts was done in February this
year, according to the deputy minister. 
</P>
