<HEADLINE> Li Peng Dismisses So-called "China Threat" as </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese Premier Li
Peng dismissed here today the so-called "China threat theory" as
totally groundless, and reiterated that China will continue to
focus on the country's economic development.
</P>
<P>
Asked by a reporter from Television Corporation of Singapore
(TCS) at a joint interview with the local media on what China will
do to further develop its economic strength without causing
concerns in the neighboring nations, Premier Li pointed out that
China is pursuing an independent foreign policy of peace.
</P>
<P>
"Our defense forces are absolutely for the purpose of national
defense," Li stressed.
</P>
<P>
He said that China's development requires a peaceful and stable
international environment, especially peace in the neighboring
areas. China is putting economic development at the very center of
all its undertakings, the Premier said.
</P>
<P>
He added that China is fully aware that although its economy
has been developing at a rate of more than nine percent per annum,
the average income of the Chinese people remained low due to the
large population and the economic developments throughout the
country are uneven.
</P>
<P>
Despite the great achievements China has made since reform
started in late 1970s, it still needs dozens of years of hard work
to reach the level of the medium-developed countries in terms of
the economic development, he said.
</P>
<P>
Li is here since Sunday on a three-day official visit and will
leave for home on Tuesday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
