<HEADLINE> Li Peng Fully Confident of State-Owned Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 25 (Xinhua) -- China will take comprehensive
steps to improve efficiency of its state-owned enterprises,
visiting Chinese Premier Li Peng said here today.
</P>
<P>
"We are most confident of the progress of our state-owned
enterprises," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
In a joint interview with the local Press this afternoon, the
Premier recalled that at the National People's Congress sessions
this spring, he had put forward six-point measures to deal with
the issue, as it arouses the country's great concern.
</P>
<P>
"We cannot say all of the state-owned firms are money-losing,
for some of them are well-managed while some others are poorly
operated," Li said.
</P>
<P>
He explained that China is shifting from the centrally-planned
system to a market economy and the technology is advancing in a
continuous way.
</P>
<P>
When an enterprise goes all out to do a good job, it needs a
good mechanism, a good management team, quality products and
advanced technology, thus selling well at the market, Li added.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier, who is here on a three-day official visit,
is scheduled to leave for Beijing tomorrow afternoon by a special
plane.  
</P>
</TEXT>
