<HEADLINE> Most European Shares End With Moderate losses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Europe's two major stock markets
Paris and Frankfurt all ended slightly lower today, with London
closed for market holiday.
</P>
<P>
German stocks in Frankfurt closed lower in quiet trading, with
many unwilling to take on new positions ahead of the Bundesbank's
repo announcement Tuesday. The DAX-30 index ended 14.22 points
lower at 4,071.79.
</P>
<P>
Shares on the Paris bourse closed a touch lower on news of a
higher-than-expected rise in west German consumer prices and fears
that it could mean a rise in the Bundesbank's repo rate. The
CAC-40 index finished at 2,898.57, down 5.66 points.
</P>
<P>
The London market was closed today for a bank holiday. The FTSE
100 index ended down 76.9 points at 4,901.1 last Friday. 
</P>
