<HEADLINE> EU Distributes Teaching Materials in Cameroun </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Schools in Yaounde today
received teaching materials from the European Union (EU). The
exercise is part of the EU's program to distribute teaching
materials to 7,510 schools in Cameroun.
</P>
<P>
The teaching materials are intended to facilitate the teaching
of geometry and English language in schools in the country.
</P>
<P>
The gifts from the EU to the government of Cameroun fall
within the framework of the reinforced structural adjustment
program to ameliorate the quality of teaching techniques in
Camerounian schools.
</P>
<P>
According to the EU officials who took part in today's
distribution exercise, the EU made the choice to finance projects
in the educational sector because they see improved education as
an essential factor to achieve sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
The teaching materials distributed by the DU include rulers,
compasses and test books.
</P>
<P>
The distribution of teaching materials started in the economic
capital Douala on August 14 and the exercise will end in Menoua
on August 29.
</P>
<P>
The whole exercise is estimated to cost some 105 million CFA
francs (about 18.85 million U.S. Dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
