<DOCNO> XIE19970826.0049 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Firework Accident Injures 25 in Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Twenty five people were injured in
an unintended firework explosion late Sunday evening at a festival
in the western German city of Dortmund, local press reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The huge firework loaded with 2.2 kilograms of explosives was
fired correctly from the ground at about 23:00 Sunday evening.
Instead of exploding in the air, it dropped to the ground from a
height of about 100 meters and blew up in a crowd of spectators,
police said today.
</P>
<P>
Sixteen people who suffered from burns and shocks were
immediately brought to nearby hospitals. Another nine were treated
in ambulances on the scene. Until this evening, two of them still
remained in a special hospital.
</P>
<P>
An investigation was launched today by local authorities, but
the exact reason for the firework mulfunction was still unknown so
far. The German manufacturer of the firework, Nico
Feuerwerktechnik, said a similar accident had never occurred in
Germany before.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
