<HEADLINE> Peace Urged for Economic Development in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Cape Verde Minister of
Health, Labor and Social Affairs Joao Medina today said Angola
must realize peace to boost its social and economic development.
</P>
<P>
He made the statement to the press here after a meeting with
Angola's Acting Prime Minister Castro Loy.
</P>
<P>
Blessed with rich natural resources, Angola will find its road
for social and economic advancement and make its contributions to
the world, especially to Africa after peace returns to the
country, Medina noted.
</P>
<P>
On bilateral relations, Medina said, Angolan Foreign Minister
Venancio de Moura's forthcoming visit to Cape Verde on Wednesday
and the visit by Cape Verde' Prime Minister Carlos Veiga to
Angola on September 7 will usher in a new stage of the bilateral
ties of cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The enhanced relations between the two countries will be
conducive to the stability in both the region and the African
continent, but to the livelihood of the peoples of the two
countries as well, he said.
</P>
<P>
Medina arrived in Luanda on August 20 for a one-week working
visit to the country, in a bid to promote bilateral cooperation
in the social spheres. 
</P>
