<HEADLINE> Turkey Drives Further Away from EU, Says Greek FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Greece's Foreign Minister
Theodoros Pangalos today warned that Turkey was driving itself
further away from the European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
He made the warning while commenting on Sunday's statements by
Turkish European Union and Cypriot Affairs Minister Sukru Gurel
that Turkey would consider withdrawing its application for full
accession to the EU unless the union included Ankara in the first
round of EU expansion.
</P>
<P>
Pangalos said that no progress could be made in this way between
Turkey and the EU.
</P>
<P>
Ankara was driving itself to "marginalization", he said, adding
that this was not designed by Athens, which favors the development
of the neighboring country's European orientation.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Greek government spokesman Dimitris Reppas today
also said that Turkey was far away from meeting even the most
basic criteria for equal participation into the EU. 
</P>
