<HEADLINE> Italian Takes Women's Individual Foil Gold at Universiade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Italy, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Italy's Atlanta Olympic
Silver medallist Valentina Vezzali overwhelmed her compatriot Anna
Giacometti 15-9 in the final to win the women's individual foil gold
medal at the 19th World University Games here on Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
Giacometti, runner-up of this year's Mediterraneo Games, took the
silver medal.
</P>
<P>
In the earlier semi-finals, Vezzali defeated China's Xiao Aihua,
sixth place of last year's Olympic Games, 12-10 after nine minutes of
play while Giacometti beat hungarian Ildiko Mincza, former European
champion, 15-8.
</P>
<P>
Both Xiao and Mincza got the bronze medal.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 fencers from 14 countries competed in the individual
event.
</P>
<P>
After five days of fencing cometition, Italy won two gold medals
while Cuba, Ukraine and Hungary took one gold each.
</P>
<P>
According to fencing competition schedule, the men's foil team
event will be held on Tuesday.  
</P>
