<HEADLINE> Outstanding Chinese Young People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Ten young Chinese people,
selected from a group of 54 candidates, were honored today as
being the "Nation's Top 10 Outstanding Young People".
</P>
<P>
The election was jointly sponsored by the All-China Youth
Federation, the China Youth Development Foundation, and ten
Beijing-based mass media organizations.
</P>
<P>
The lucky winners were Wu Lan, a female doctor practicing both
Chinese and Mongolian Medicine in north China's Inner Mogolia
Autonomous Region; Ye Long, president of the Shida Computer Group
Co. Ltd. in Fujian Province; Fen Gong, an actor with the China
Broadcasting Art Troupe; Li Yongbo, head coach of China Badminton
Team; Li Jianbo, a professor with the Material Sciences and
Engineering Department at Qinghua University; Wu Guodi, president
of the Zhejiang Province branch of the China Light Industry Group;
Shen Fangquan, a battlion commander with the Second Artillery
Force; Zhao Mantang, a research fellow in Tianshui City, Gansu
Province; Zhan Lianchuan, a captain with the Armed Police Force in
Shangdong Province; and Jian Chunlin, director of a state-owned
farm in Hainan Province. 
</P>
