<DOCNO> XIE19970826.0066 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> London Voted Best City for Business in UK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 26 (Xinhua) -- London, the British capital, is
regarded as the most popular location in Britain for companies for
the second year running, according to a survey published today.
</P>
<P>
The survey, conducted by Black Horse, a relocation company,
said that Birmingham also retains its second place while
Manchester is in the third place.
</P>
<P>
Black Horse asked 1,000 businessmen to grade cities according
to a range of relocation factors, including the cost and quality
of local resources, transport, the business environment, the
personal quality of life, government incentives and the quality of
potential local clients.
</P>
<P>
Brighton, the Sussex seaside town, is rated as the least
popular city for business, trailing behind Dudley, in the West
Midlands, and Halifax, in West Yorkshire.
</P>
<P>
Availability of a quality workforce was ranked as the top
priority for companies on the move by nearly 50 percent of those
who took part in the survey as it is vital to the success of any
business, large or small, said the director of Black Horse Richard
Day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
