<HEADLINE> Bus Services for HK New Airport Nailed Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 26 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Airport
Authority (AA) today signed an agreement on the operation of
airside bus services at the New Airport now under construction at
Chek Lap Kok, a tiny island in the west of the Hong Kong Island.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Hong Kong Airport Services Ltd. (HAS),
jointly owned by two local airlines, will become the only bus
carrier at the New Airport to transport passengers between the
terminal building and aircraft at apron parking areas. The
services will start in tandem with the commencement of the airport
operations in April 1998, and last for ten years.
</P>
<P>
HAS will also provide regular airside shuttle services for
staff of the AA, government, tenants, licensees and franchisees
working at the airport.
</P>
<P>
HAS is expected to pour an initial investment of approximately
75 million HK dollars (about 10 million US dollars) to launch the
services. The company has ordered 16 buses from Germany.  
</P>
