<HEADLINE> Qiongzhou Straits Railway Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, August 26 (Xinhua) -- The Guangdong-Hainan Railway Co.,
which became operational today, will build and operate a railway
line linking south China's Guangdong Province and the island
province of Hainan.
</P>
<P>
The company, jointly funded by the Ministry of Railways and the
two provinces, will begin the construction of the project within
the year.
</P>
<P>
The project will be completed within three years at an
estimated cost of 4.5 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The line, the country's first cross-channel railway line, will
include a Zhanjiang-Xuwen County Line in Guangdong, a train ferry
across the Qiongzhou Straits, and railway from Haikou to
Changjiang County in Hainan.
</P>
<P>
The train ferry will have a designed deadweight capacity of
4,600 tons. The whole railway line is expected to have an annual
handling capacity of eight million tons of cargos by the year 2000
and 10.2 million tons by 2010.
</P>
<P>
Hainan Province has set a goal of handling 26 million tons of
cargos to and from island by the year by 2000, most of which will
be transported via the railway line.  
</P>
</TEXT>
