<HEADLINE> Cuba, Ukraine in Men's Foil Team Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Cuba edged hosts Italy while
Ukraine beat back the challenge from China to set up a final showdown
in the men's foil team event here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban team, including the gold and silver medalists from the
world championships held in Cape Town in July, beat the high-spirited
Italians 45-42.
</P>
<P>
In the other semi-final match between Ukraine and China, Ukraine
led all the way and eventually wrapped up the match 45-37.
</P>
<P>
Cuba and Ukraine are the best two teams in the Universiade fencing
tournament. The team foil final will be the third encounter between
the two countries at the Universiade fencing tournament.
</P>
<P>
In the two previous encounters between the two countries, Cuba won
the men's individual foil title while Ukraine claimed the gold of the
men's individual epee event.
</P>
<P>
The third-place playoff of the team foil is underway between Italy
and China. 
</P>
