<HEADLINE> China's Top Planning Official Talks on Economic Situation (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- The added value of the industrial businesses reached 1,152
billion yuan between January and July, 11 percent more than in the
same 1996 period.
</P>
<P>
-- China's export volume reached 96.4 billion US dollars
between January and July, up 26.1 percent. By the end of July,
China's foreign exchange reserve reached 125.9 billion US dollars,
20.9 billion US dollars more than that in the same 1996
period. Exchange rates between the Chinese currency Renminbi and
major foreign currencies have also kept stable.
</P>
<P>
-- The national revenue has increased by 29 percent while expenditure
rose by 20.5 percent in this period.
</P>
<P>
-- China's urban residents had the average income of 2,623 yuan
and rural Chinese 980 yuan, up 2.6 percent and 3.3 percent,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
-- Total volume of retail sales of consumer goods reached
1510.9 billion yuan, 13.8 percent increase or 12 percent rise
after deducting price fluctuations.  
</P>
