<HEADLINE> Chinese Companies to Consolidate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Four companies from different
industrial sectors in east China's Jiangsu Province are planning
to improve market competitiveness by consolidating into one
petrochemical enterprise group.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo attended today's preliminary
organizational meeting.
</P>
<P>
The planned Petrochemical Industries Group will consist of the
top four petrochemical companies in Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
The four enterprises have established close cooperative
relations and the consolidation will ensure improved efficiency
and better use of assets. Wu noted that the State Council has
approved establishment of the group
</P>
<P>
The new group will have total assets of 45 billion yuan and
annual sales of 33 billion yuan, will become the nation's leading
producer of oil products, chemical fertilizer, and polyester
products. It will also be the country's largest base for
petroleum, chemicals, fertilizer, and chemical fiber.
</P>
<P>
The form of establishing larger and stronger enterprise groups
will help improve China's economic structure and improve the
distribution of resources, said Wu, adding that the practice
should be gradually expanded, rather than rushing headlong into
action. 
</P>
</TEXT>
