<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on India's BSE Gains 59.57 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 26 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market today gained 59.57 points to
4,107.24 as against the previous close of 4,047.67.
</P>
<P>
The national index also rose by 21.72 points to 1,791.01 from
previous close of 1,769.29.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and US dollar index were quoted up at 401.76 and
183.91 compared with previous close of 397.55 and 183.45
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Speculatives staged a smart recovery pushing the sensitive
index up by over 59 points on the BSE market today following
emergence of buying by domestic institutions and shortcovering by
operators.
</P>
<P>
Brokers also attributed the rally to the fact that the decision
on the hike in prices of petroleum products had been deferred for
some more time.  
</P>
