<HEADLINE> Minister on China's Telecom Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 26 (Xinhua) -- China needs vast amounts of
overseas funding to expand telecommunications services, but is not
as yet fully prepared to open its massive telecom market to
foreign firms, according to Posts and Telecommunications Minister
Wu Jichuan.
</P>
<P>
However, the Chinese government is preparing to improve
conditions needed to open the market to foreign businesses at the
earliest possible date, Wu said at a press conference here today.
</P>
<P>
Wu indicated that substantial amounts of state-of-the-art
foreign telecommunications technology and equipment have entered
China's open telecom equipment market. He also noted that
foreign-funded projects launched on the basis of reciprocity and
mutual benefit are encouraged in the market.
</P>
<P>
China's posts and telecommunications sector recorded 80.91
billion yuan in turnover for the first half of this year, up 32.9
percent on the 1996 period. 
</P>
