<HEADLINE> Tianjin Conducts Joint Marine Rescue Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, August 26 (Xinhua) -- The Tianjin Marine Rescue Center
conducted a joint rescue exercise today in the Bohai Bay near
Dagukou in the north China port city of Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
Seven rescues ships and a helicopter participated in the
exercise along with 100 professional rescue workers.
</P>
<P>
The ships and helicopter completed their task ensuring that
"sinking" barge disconnected from a tugboat in heavy winds and
high waves remained afloat.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the exercise was to improve center's ability to
respond to marine accidents in bad weather conditions, said Wang
Huaifeng, director of the Tianjin Sea Monitoring Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Personnel from the flight service team under the government of
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region participated in exercise
and demonstrated expertise in using helicopters to rescue seamen
involved in marine accidents. 
</P>
