<HEADLINE> China's Top Planning Official Talks on Economic Situation (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 26 (Xinhua) -- China's top economic planning
official said today that China has achieved "best economic
situation in the recent years" after deepening the reform on
businesses and economic restructuring.
</P>
<P>
The national economy has maintained the appropriately fast and
comparatively stable growth, while the commodity prices have
fallen at a fairly low level, Chen Jinhua, minister in charge of
the State Planning Commission, said at the 27th meeting of the
Standing Committee of the Eighth National People's Congress (NPC)
on the national economic development in the past seven months this
year.
</P>
<P>
He said that the overall economic situation is illustrated
in following aspects:
</P>
<P>
-- China's gross domestic product (GDP) reached 3,318 billion
yuan (nearly 400 billion US dollars) in the first half of the
year, 9.5 percent more than that in the same period of 1996. New
successes were achieved in production, construction, circulation
and finance.
</P>
<P>
-- The grain growing areas this year were about 112.6 million
hectares, 400,000 hectares more than last year. Summer grain
output reached 123.95 billion kilograms, 10.75 billion kilograms
more than last year, hitting an all-time high.
</P>
