<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Telecom Enjoys Rapid Growth (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Puge Yi Nationality Autonomous
County, western Sichuan Province, joined the national
program-controlled telephone network today, becoming the last
county in the nation to do so.
</P>
<P>
China currently has more than 100 million program-controlled
telephone lines.
</P>
<P>
The achievement has established a major milestone in the
development of Chinese telecommunications construction, said Wu
Jichuan, minister of posts and telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
During an exclusive interview with Xinhua News Agency, Wu said
that China's telecommunications sector can no longer be
categorized as a bottleneck industry, and that the sector's
development has "appropriately surpassed that of national economic
development."
</P>
<P>
The expansion of China's telephone network, developed at a rate
rarely seen in the world, has created the second largest such
network in the world, following the United States, said Wu.
</P>
<P>
China's telephone network capacity jumped from less than 15
million telephones at the end of 1991 to more than 100 million
telephones last year.
</P>
<P>
"The capacity does not as yet include Hong Kong, Macao and
Taiwan," according to Wu.
</P>
<P>
As late as 1978, nearly 300 Chinese citizens shared a
telephone, with the current figure standing at 22 phones per 300
people. In cities, however, the rate stands at one phone per four
people.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970826.0110 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Telecom Enjoys Rapid Growth (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
All Chinese provincial capitals have at least seven digit phone
numbers, with eight digits used in Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou,
Chongqing and Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
Wu projected that China will increase its program-controlled
switchboard capacity to 174 million telephones by the end of the
century, with one in ten people owning a telephone.
</P>
<P>
The country's mobile telephone network has developed at an
annual rate of 149 percent over the past five years, with the rate
far exceeding that for regular telephones, Wu pointed out that
some 10.26 million people currently own mobile telephones.
</P>
<P>
"Mobile telecommunications has emerged as a new growth area for
China's telecommunications industry," said Wu.
</P>
<P>
China's analogue mobile telecom network covers all county-level
cities and a number of towns. In addition, the nation's digital
mobile phone network not only covers the entire country, but also
has linked to networks in France, Germany, Australia, Singapore
and eight other countries.
</P>
<P>
China plans to develop automatic roaming services with six
countries, including Spain, Turkey, Finland and Denmark.
</P>
<P>
Wu also pointed to the great progress in the technological
development of the telecom industry over the past five years.
</P>
<P>
More than half of program-controlled switchboards used in China
are produced domestically, including some 87 percent of
program-controlled switchboards added in 1996.
</P>
<P>
China has developed a network which includes a primary cable
network and subsidiary digital microwave and satellite systems.
</P>
<P>
"Completion of the Lanzhou-Xining-Lhasa cable network next year
will link China's trunk cable network to the 'roof of the world',"
according to Wu.
</P>
<P>
China plans to build a nationwide telecommunications grid by
the end of the century.
</P>
<P>
Wu summarized the past five years of development by saying:
"China's telecom industry has without a doubt witnessed the most
rapid and dynamic period of development in history."
</P>
<P>
China's posts and telecommunications business volume grew by an
annual rate of 45.6 percent during the 1992-1996 period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970826.0111 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Safety Techniques Used for Australian-Made Car </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Australian car producer Holden
said today that it has developed and introduced benchmark
techniques that could provide better safety protection for car
occupants.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the launch of Holden's new model VT Commodore in
Sydney, Laurie Sparke, the company's safety expert, said "two
significant new technologies have been developed and applied for
the first time, achieving better crash energy management and
improved protection through a sophisticated restraint system."
</P>
<P>
A key to the car's safety performance was the
computer-optimized restraint system, which links driver and
passenger airbags with the seat belt webbing clamps and
pyrotechnic pretensioners.
</P>
<P>
Using a new computer program, Holden simulated 100,000 crashes
with various combination of occupants, safety features and crash
circumstances, something that was not possible before, Sparke
said.
</P>
<P>
The expert said the second major safety breakthrough on the VT
was the introduction of new frame design which allowed the front
end of the new Commodore to crush in a more progressive manner,
absorbing more crash energy.
</P>
<P>
The technology is applicable to rear wheel drive models like
the Commodore, the last rear wheel drive passenger car in the
General Motors world.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970826.0112 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Minister on Reform, Economic Construction (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 26 (Xinhua) -- China has achieved great success
in reform and economic construction since the 14th National
Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) in October 1992,
Chen Jinhua, minister in charge of the State Planning Commission,
said today.
</P>
<P>
Chen made the remark while delivering a report on China's
achievements in reform and economic construction organized by
five central departments.
</P>
<P>
China entered a new round of high economic growth during the
past three year, which featured far-reaching profound
changes. Rapid economic growth has enabled China to attain the
strategic goal of quadrupling the 1980 gross national product
(GNP) by the year 2000 five years ahead of schedule, said Chen.
</P>
<P>
China also made breakthroughs in establishing a socialist
market economic structure, formed a multi-tier all-dimensional
pattern of opening up, scored notable achievements in
improving the living standards of the people, and recorded
tremendous changes in rural and urban areas.
</P>
<P>
The Eighth Five-Year Plan period (1991-1995) represented the
period with most rapid growth and the smallest fluctuations since
the founding of New China in 1949, according to Chen.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970826.0113 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Minister on Reform, Economic Construction (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chen added that that successful implementation of the Eighth
Five-Year Plan laid a solid foundation for drawing up the Ninth
Five-Year Plan (1996-2000) and the program for the long-term
objective through the year of 2010.
</P>
<P>
So far, China's economy has achieved a "soft landing", thereby
demonstrating a fine development momentum characterized by "high
growth and low inflation".
</P>
<P>
The minister noted that rapid development over the past five
years has led to historical changes in China's economic life, with
the market force playing an increasingly important role in the
resources distribution.
</P>
<P>
The relationship between supply and demand has changed greatly
over the years. Supply and demand have either remained in balance,
or the the former has exceeded the latter for the majority of
commodities. This in turn has led to the appearance of a buyer's
market, accompanied by the disappearance of long-standing
phenomena such as standing in queues to purchase commodities and
rationing.
</P>
<P>
Changes have also taken place in the relationship between
industry and agriculture, with a reversal in the one-way situation
in which the latter provided the former with accumulation. Today,
the industrial sector also provides aid to agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Successes in economic construction, reform and opening since
the 14th congress prove that the the Chinese Communist Party
Central Committee headed by Jiang Zemin has the full ability to
administer the country effectively, skillfully control the
macro-economy and handle complicated issues, said Chen.
</P>
<P>
The minister also stressed the need to become sober-minded in
solving a number of evident problems cropping up in current social
and economic life. 
</P>
</TEXT>
