<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Consumer Price Index on Rise in Angola's Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 26 (Xinhua) -- The consumer price index (CPI)
in Angola's capital Luanda rose by 12.9 percent in the first
seven months this year, according to a press communique released
here today by Angola's National Statistical Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The communique said that the CPI increased by 1.35 percent in
July in comparision with that of June due to the depreciation of
the Angolan currency Kwanza by 30 percent against the U.S.
Dollar, which fell to 265,000 Kwanza against the dollar from
209,000 against the dollar.
</P>
<P>
It said that the CPI in the capital registered a 112.6 percent
rise during the period from July 1996 to July this year.
</P>
<P>
One third of the Angolan habitants live in the capital region.
Therefore, the changes of the CPI in this region is a barametor
reflecting the prices in the whole market of Angola. 
</P>
</TEXT>
