<HEADLINE> HK's Oldest TV Magazine Closes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 26 (Xinhua) -- One of Hong Kong's oldest
television guides, TV Weekly, will cease publication as a result
of persistent losses.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese-language TV Weekly will close after its 1,556th
issue, which goes on sale tomorrow, announced TVE Publications,
the owner.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the company said the closure is a necessary
marketing strategy, and is partly a result of constant losses.
</P>
<P>
He said the company will concentrate its business on the
remaining five magazines, with plans to expand into the mainland
and Taiwan markets.
</P>
<P>
Founded in November 1967, TV Weekly was one of Hong Kong's
first TV magazines. The company was bought by the South China
Morning Post last year from TVB.  
