<HEADLINE> ADB Grants Loan to Fiji to Improve Roads </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 26 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
today approved a 50 million U.S. dollar loan to improve the road
network in Fiji, an archipelago state in the South Pacific.
</P>
<P>
The loan will be used to upgrade and rehabilitate 180
kilometers of roads on four islands, and improve safety on
national roads, the Manila-based multilateral financial body said
in a press release.
</P>
<P>
The ADB is also providing Fiji with a 1.4 million dollar
technical assistance grant financed through the Japan Special Fund
to support road sector reforms and safety improvements.
</P>
<P>
This aid will be used to reorganize the Fijian Public Works
Department, establish a land transport authority, and implement a
road safety action plan.
</P>
<P>
Fiji's road network is largely complete but some roads need
sealing or maintaining, the ADB said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
