Standing Committee of China's National People's Congress (NPC),
met here today with a delegation from the Mongolian People's
Revolutionary Party (MPRP), led by Enkhtuvshin, a member of the
MPRP Governing Council and secretary of the MPRP Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Buhe said that China and Mongolia are good neighbors, and that
there is a long history of friendly relations between the two
countries and between the Communist Party of China (CPC) and the
MPRP.
</P>
<P>
He said that exchanges between the two parties have contributed
to the growth of bilateral ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Buhe said he hopes that the CPC and the MPRP will expand their
relations on the basis of four principles governing party-to-party
relations, namely, independence, equality, mutual respect and
non-interference in each other's internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
China respects the path of development taken by the Mongolian
people, he noted, expressing the hope that friendly relations
between the two countries and their parliaments will keep growing.
</P>
<P>
Buhe also briefed the visitors on China's reform and opening-up
drive, and its economic advancement as well as the major work of
the NPC.
</P>
<P>
Enkhtuvshin said that the MPRP and the CPC enjoy long-standing
friendly exchanges, and that their relations are in the
fundamental interests of the people of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He added that his party places great importance on its
relations with the CPC, and on developing good-neighborly and
co-operative ties with China, noting that the MPRP is willing to
make efforts to promote bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
The Mongolian visitors arrived here Monday to start their
weekly visit to China as guests of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, Dai Bingguo, head of the International
Department of the CPC Central Committee, met with the delegation.
</P>
