<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Post Office to Launch Disk Mail Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 26 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Post Office will
launch a new service later this year which will allow businesses to
hand over floppy disks to the Post Office to print out information
and mail directly to their clients.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Post Office said on Monday that the service
had successfully passed a trial with the Rating and Valuation
Department in June.
</P>
<P>
He said customers could give disks to the Post Office, which
would print out the documents, then envelope and send them to
clients. The new service will save the sender a lot of time and
effort in printing and posting.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the Post Office is also actively exploring
the use of the Internet, including the revolutionary idea of
selling stamps via cyberspace. He said surfers might one day be
able to download and print stamps from the Internet.
</P>
<P>
Despite intensive competition from private couriers and new
communication technology, the mail volume through the Post Office
rose by four percent last year, he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
