preparing for the Sudanese peace talks, which presidential aide
Parks Mankahlana said on Monday, could take place as "early as
this weekend".
</P>
<P>
Mandela last week said he hoped to host peace talks between
Sudanese president Omar Al Bashir and rebel leader Garang, who
heads the largest southern-based guerrilla movement in Sudan.
