<HEADLINE> Vietnam Establishes Securities Commission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam set up the State
Securities Commission Monday, marking an important turning point
in formation and development of the country's capital market,
local reports said today.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese government hoped that Vietnam's securities
market would become a major channel for attracting long-term
capital for enterprises, particularly those in key economic areas.
</P>
<P>
The Securities Commission is expected to compile legal
documents on securities and stock markets, coordinate with
concerned agencies to organize and develop a stock market and
supervise activities of stock exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Vietnamese Deputy Prime Minister Phan Van Khai said that the
set-up of the securities market has met the need of the
development of market economy.
</P>
<P>
He said the role of the government is to help form the
securities market in an orderly manner and ensure its operation in
a sound and efficient way.
</P>
<P>
He urged the State Securities Commission to build regulatory
bodies necessary for a new stock market.
</P>
<P>
Local observers predicted that at least two years are needed
for Vietnam to have the stock market operate officially. 
</P>
</TEXT>
