<HEADLINE> Australian Bourse Drifts Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 26 (Xinhua) -- The Australian share market
drifted lower in a day of uninspired trading as investors remained
on the sidelines awaiting further direction out of the United
States, brokers said.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index closed 10.8 percents weaker at 2626.3,
after the Down Jones industrial average closed 28.34 points lower
overnight at 7859.57.
</P>
<P>
The all resources index shed three points to finish at 1384.8
while the industrials sector fared worse, with the all industrials
index losing 20.3 points to 4219.8.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was a modest 295.94 million shares, valued at
655.96 million Australian dollars (485.41 million U.S. dollars),
with falls outpacing rises by 584 to 450, and 453 steady.
</P>
<P>
Resources heavyweight BHP climbed three cents to 17.23
Australian dollars, Rio Tinto fell 27 cents to 20.23 Australian
dollars and WMC rose 14 cents to 7.18 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the industrials index, Coca Cola fell 40 cents to 14.80
Australian dollars, Coles Myer slipped 14 cents to 6.35 Australian
dollars, brewery giant Foster's was down 4 cents to 2.58
Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the banking sector, National Australia Bank closed 6 cents
lower at 19.04 Australian dollars, Westpac Banking Corp. was down
7 cents to 8.05 Australian dollars, ANZ, another major bank, also
lost 7 cents to 10.00 Australian dollars, CBA fell 12 cents to
15.21 Australian dollars and Macquarie finished 20 cents weaker at
13.35 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The top traded stock was options in gold explorer Taipan
Resources, with 12.77 million shares changing hands worth 272,513
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The gold index dipped 1.3 points to 1355.7, while bullion in
Sydney was traded 0.35 U.S. dollars lower at 324.15 U.S. dollars.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
