<HEADLINE>   Australian Dollar Closes Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 26 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar closed a
touch lower against the U.S. dollar with little local news to
inspire movement in the market.
</P>
<P>
The local currency was confined to a narrow range of 74.63 U.S.
cents to 74.75 U.S. cents and it closed at 74.73 U.S. cents, down
from its finish locally Monday of 74.78 U.S. cents.
</P>
<P>
