George Bank, said good Australian dollar buying was still
occurring at the 74.50 U.S. cent level, with sellers in the market
at 75.00 U.S. cents.
</P>
<P>
He said Monday night's UK bank holiday had continued to subdue
local trade today and this afternoon dealers had been waiting to
see if Germany's Bundesbank made an announcement on raising
interest rates.
</P>
<P>
Shortly after the Australian market's close, the Bundesbank
announced it had left the repo rate unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar finished at 88.57 Japanese yen, up from
Monday's 88.35 yen and against the German mark it was at 1.3598,
up from 1.3595. 
