<DOCNO> XIE19970826.0150 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Reports Rapid Growth In Foreign Trade (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 26 (Xinhua) -- China's foreign trade has
recovered from last year's slump, with 96.4 billion US dollars
worth of exports in the first seven months of the year, a 26
percent increase.
</P>
<P>
The country expects to handle a total of 400 billion US dollars
in imports and exports annually by the end of the century.
</P>
<P>
The country suffered a drop in exports last year, and reported
an increase of only 1.5 percent for the whole of 1996, the lowest
since the reform and opening-up drive began in 1979.
</P>
<P>
Foreign trade expert Li Yushi attributes the recovery to
timely export rebates and stable prices on the domestic market.
</P>
<P>
Last year, there was 30 billion yuan in refunds for
export-oriented enterprises, greatly helping improve their
financial situation.
</P>
<P>
Successful macro-economic controls also helped stabilize
prices, lowering the cost of exports and increasing
competitiveness of commodities.
</P>
<P>
But to increase foreign trade, a greater effort must be made to
improve the product mix, because some enterprises are running at
a loss, Li said.
</P>
<P>
China has had a shift in the export structure from primary
products to manufactured goods, which now account for nearly 85
percent of exports. But a further goal is to develop value-added
products to get a larger market share, and priority has been
placed on electronics products and machinery. China has advantages
in this area, especially in generators, and cement and chemical
industry equipment.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970826.0151 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Reports Rapid Growth in Foreign Trade (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the first seven months of the year, China had slightly over
30 billion US dollars worth of machinery and electronics exports,
a rise of 24.6 percent, thanks to the government support in loans
and tax reductions.
</P>
<P>
Higher productivity is the key to steady growth in exports, Li
explained, adding that more must be done to import high-quality
raw materials, machinery, and technology to improve the quality of
Chinese products.
</P>
<P>
In the past five years, China has had a rapid increase in
imports of technology and equipment, and imported 230 billion US
dollars worth of machinery and transport equipment.
</P>
<P>
Imports of nuclear power equipment, program-controlled
telephone exchanges, and electronics goods began to increase, and
priority was given to such industries as energy,petrochemicals,
machinery and electronics.
</P>
<P>
There are now more than 5,000 enterprises with the right to
independently handle foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
The United States, Japan, and Europe remain China's major trade
partners, but the foreign trade sector is making an effort to
develop new markets in West Asia, North Africa, and Latin
America. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
