<HEADLINE> Economic Council to Be Set Up in Sea of Japan Regions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Leaders of local authorities in
four countries bordering the Sea of Japan agreed in Tottori,
northwest of Tokyo, today, to set up a joint council to promote
economic cooperation among them.
</P>
<P>
The heads of China's Jilin Province, South Korea's Kangwon
Province, Russia's Maritime Province and Japan's Tottori
Prefecture reached the accord at an international forum to discuss
mutual exchanges in the Sea of Japan region, Kyodo News reported.
</P>
<P>
Other topics to be discussed at the forum include the building
of a transportation network through the use of chartered
airplanes, and the creation of a mechanism under which experts can
exchange information on protection of the environment around the
Sea of Japan.
</P>
<P>
Tottori Governor Yuji NIshio recommended representatives of
Mongolia and the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) also
be invited to take part in the project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
