<HEADLINE> Chinese, Laotian Foreign Minister Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 26 (Xinhua) -- China's Vice-Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen, meeting with his Laotian counterpart,
Somsavat Lengsavad here today, said that China is ready to
establish long-term, stable and good-neighborly friendly relations
for the next century with Laos based on the Five Principles of
Peaceful Coexistence.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that China and Laos have a great deal to share and a
solid foundation for promoting bilateral relations, and that the
people of the two countries are neighbors linked by mountains and
rivers, with a long history of friendship.
</P>
<P>
Since the normalization of bilateral relations in 1989,
friendly co-operation in various fields has resumed and developed,
Qian said, expressing satisfaction with the smooth growth in
bilateral good-neighborly relations and friendly co-operation.
</P>
<P>
He said that China appreciates the "one China" position of Laos
and its consistent support of the Chinese people's great cause of
peaceful reunification.
</P>
<P>
The Laotian foreign minister said he agrees with Qian's view on
bilateral relations and that the growth of good-neighborly ties
between the two countries in recent years has provided
opportunities for two peoples, especially for those living in the
border areas.
</P>
<P>
The signing of a supplementary protocol to a border treaty by
China and Laos will bring the peaceful and friendly border into
the 21st century, Somsavat said.
</P>
<P>
The two foreign ministers signed the protocol after the talks.
</P>
<P>
Somsavat arrived on Monday for the official good-will visit at
Qian's invitation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
