<HEADLINE> Ramos Creates Civil Aviation Consultative Council </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
today ordered the creation of the Civil Aviation Consultative
Council to enhance the cooperation between the government and the
private sector on policies and programs on civil aviation.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said one of the main functions of the council is to make
recommendations serving as inputs in the formulation of government
policies and programs on the local aviation industry.
</P>
<P>
The council will also identify and recommend legislative
measures necessary in the development of the industry and provide
a forum for the resolution of issues affecting the industry's
competitiveness, he said.
</P>
<P>
The council was put under the administrative supervision of the
Department of Transportation and Communications.  
