<HEADLINE> Cob Castro Wins WBO Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Melchor Cob Castro of Mexico
succeeded in his challenging bout against compatriot defending WBO
flyweight champion Jesus Chong on Monday in Inglewood, California.
</P>
<P>
Cob Castro, 29, won by point advantage in the 12-round fight,
though he was cut over his left eye in the 10th round. His low
blows in the sixth and 11th rounds dominated through the uneven
bout.
</P>
<P>
Cob Castro, who weighed in 49 kilograms, has ran his record to
50-5-4 with 21 knockouts, while the 32-year-old Chong dropped to
31-8 with 27 knockouts.
</P>
<P>
On the undercard, NABO junior middleweight champion Rodney
Jones of the United States won his compatriot Tim Shocks in the
12th round, scoring his 13th straight win.
</P>
<P>
Jones improved his match record to 18-2 with 10th knockout,
while Shocks dropped to 17-4. 
</P>
