<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0830 GMT, August 26 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA -- Juma Oris, the leader of the West Nile Bank Front
(WNBF), has been put under house arrest since July in southern
Sudan, "The New Vision" reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Siraj Taba Kaka, a former rebel of the Uganda National Rescue
Front Part Two (UNRF ii) surrendered to the government troops
earlier this month. Oris refused to obey the demand to cooperate
with Ali Bamuze, the leader of UNRF ii. (Uganda-House Arrest)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SINGAPORE -- Chinese Premier Li Peng said Tuesday the
cooperation between China and ASEAN countries should be oriented
toward the 21st century on the basis of mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
In a speech entitled "Strengthen Mutually Beneficial
Cooperation and Promote Common Prosperity", delivered to a group
of Singapore businessmen on the last day of his three-day visit,
Li said China and the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
(ASEAN) countries need to expand areas of cooperation in order for
their respective strength to complement each other.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China and ASEAN countries also need to strengthen
coordination and cooperation in the financial field.
(China-ASEAN-Cooperation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SINGAPORE -- Chinese Premier Li Peng left here Tuesday for
home by special plane after wounding up his three-day official
visit to Singapore.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier arrived in Singapore, the last leg of his
two-nation Southeast Asian tour, on Sunday as guest of Singaporean
Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong. Li visited Malaysia on August 21-24.
(Chinese Premier-Singapore-Leave)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- Thailand is sticking firmly to its own offers to
financial liberalization under its commitment to the World Trade
Organization (WTO), as the United States presses further on the
matter before the WTO opens the next round of talks on financial
services in September.
</P>
<P>
Chaiyawat Wibulswasdi, governor of the Bank of Thailand, said
Monday that Thailand has opened its financial market sufficiently
and it will stand firm with its original offers.
</P>
<P>
The Thai government has issued new bank licenses to foreign
banks recently and it also has allowed foreign banks to install
automatic teller machines (ATMs) and expand their branches in the
country, he said. (Thailand-Financial Liberalization)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SARAJEVO -- Momcilo Krajisnik, the Serb member of the Bosnian
Presidency, refused to attend a presidential session Monday,
citing reasons related to the political crisis in Republika Srpska.
</P>
<P>
Krajisnik did not show up at the scheduled meeting of the
presidency but sent a letter to his colleagues saying that he is
temporarily prevented from taking part in its work, said Mirza
Hajric, an advisor to Alija Izetbegovic, Muslim member and
chairman of the presidency. (Bosnia-Krajisnik-Refuse) 
</P>
</TEXT>
