<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan, Tatarstan to Promote Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA-ATA, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Kazakh President Nursultan
Nazarbayev said today Kazakhstan has attached great importance to
cooperation with the Russian Federation in economy, culture and
science and technology.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with visiting Tatar President Mintimer
Shaimiyev, the two leaders discussed the prospects for enhancing
cooperation between Kazakhstan and Tatarstan, which is a republic
of Russia, within the framework of the Kazakh-Russian agreement on
friendship, cooperation and mutual aid signed in 1992.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed that Kazakhstan and Tatarstan have great
potentiality in economic and trade cooperation. Kazakhstan will
import petro-chemical products, equipment for oil industry and
various civil products, while Tatarstan will import nonferrous
metal, fur and grain from Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
Kazakh Prime Minister Akezhan Kazhegeldin today signed an
agreement with Shaimiyev on opening a Tatar Office of the Charge
d'Affaires in Kazakhstan, which both sides said to help improve
development of the bilateral cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
