<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Little Changed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, August 26 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand share market
ended little changed today in moderate volume.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index rose only half a point to 2489 with a turnover
of 55 million NZ dollars (35 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Gains in some leaders helped offset the falls in many small
companies. Telecom shares picked up 6 cents to 770 cents. Also
higher were Fletcher Building, up 1 cent to 435 cents, Carter Holt
Harvey, rising 3 cents to 339 cents and Lion Nathan, climbing 4
cents to 404 cents.
</P>
<P>
But Air New Zealand lost 1 cent to 292 cents and Brierley
Investment stayed unchanged at 137 cents.
</P>
<P>
Overall, there were 36 rises and 66 falls.  
