<HEADLINE> Foreign Minister Meets German Parliamentary Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen met with a delegation from Germany's
Parliamentary Group of the Christian Democratic Union/the
Christian Social Union led by its Vice-Chairman Rudolf Seiters, at
the Diaoyutai State Guest House here today.
</P>
<P>
Qian told the group that at a time when the world is becoming
polarized, a new concept of security needs to be established, and
that, "Increasing defense expenditures and strengthening military
blocs are no way to safeguard security."
</P>
<P>
He said that the countries of the world should build friendly
co-operative relations based on common interests. "This is the key
to safeguarding security," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also told the German guests that China will continue its
reforms and opening to the outside world and that it will continue
along the path of building socialism with Chinese characteristics
that Deng Xiaoping initiated.
</P>
<P>
Seiters said that maintaining stability and development of
China is in the interest of the country and the world as a whole,
and that he wishes China success in its development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
