<HEADLINE> North China Municipality's Information Port Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin municipality will become
a north China information hub and equipment manufacturing base by
the year 2010, according to mayor Zhang Lichang.
</P>
<P>
Zhang told an international information port forum that Tianjin
is far from satisfied with its role as north China's largest
comprehensive port, and wants to work on becoming another kind of
port: an information port.
</P>
<P>
He said that the 21st century will be the information age, and
because of Tianjin's location, human resources and solid
industrial base, it has many advantages in this area.
</P>
<P>
Work has begun on its information port construction, for a tax
management system, science and technology information network, and
economic information system.
</P>
<P>
The work will have two phases. The first, from 1997 to 2000,
will be on a telecommunication and information exchange
network. The second phase, from 2001 to 2010, will be
infrastructure for the information industry.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
