<HEADLINE> Graf Hopes Playing in Australian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 25 (Xinhua) -- German Steffi Graf, five-time
U.S. Open champion, made her appearance at the U.S. Open on Monday
without her title-defending task, saying she hopes to play the
Australian Open.
</P>
<P>
Graf, ranked seventh currently in the world, dedicated herself
with other former world champions to the new Arthur Ashe Stadium
and showed her willingness to come back to the court.
</P>
<P>
"I'll definitely be ready for next year," said the former world
number one, who suffered from the April knee injury. "When I come
back, I want to really be fit and healthy. I'm gunning for the
Australian Open."
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old, winner of this tournament in 1988, 1989, 1993,
1995 and 1996, played only five tournaments this season and won
just once.
</P>
<P>
Martina Hingis, 16-year-old Swiss, took over the world number
one ranking during Graf's absence and won in the Australian Open
and Wimbledon. 
</P>
