<HEADLINE> New Airport In Central China To Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, August 26 (Xinhua) -- A new airport in Zhengzhou,
capital of central China's Henan Province, is scheduled to begin
operations on August 28.
</P>
<P>
The airport, which passed a three-day state assessment on
Monday, is located 30 kilometers southeast of Zhengzhou, on 474
hectares of land. It can accommodate Boeing-747s and handle 3.8
million passengers annually.
</P>
<P>
The old Zhengzhou Airport was both a civilian and military
facility, and did not have the new airport's potential for
providing opportunities for economic development. 
