<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uganda Rebel Leader Under House Arrest in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Juma Oris, the leader of the
West Nile Bank Front (WNBF), have been put under house arrest
since July in southern Sudan, "The New Vision" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Siraj Taba Kaka, a former rebel of the Uganda National Rescue
Front Part Two (UNRF ii) surrendered to the government troops
earlier this month. Oris refused to obey the demand to cooperate
with Ali Bamuze, the leader of UNRF ii.
</P>
<P>
Siraj was the secretary of UNRF ii high command and personal
assistant to Bamuze. UNRF ii is a break-away group from the WNBF
which lost its main forces in series of fightings in southern
Sudan in March this year. Most of its remnants surrendred to
Uganda government since then. Juma Oris is the leader of WNBF.
The relations between Oris and Sudan military have soured since
the main forces of WNBF have been eliminated.
</P>
<P>
Ali Alunguru, an officer of UNRF ii, said Oris kept his
hostility to Bamuze. Loyal soldiers to Oris have been removed
from the WNBF leader.
</P>
<P>
Both Siraj and Ali are being kept in Koboko district,
north-west Uganda.
</P>
<P>
Recent reports said UNRF ii recruited hundreds of young people
for military training to fill its ranks.
</P>
<P>
Security sources in the north-west said the new development of
the matter is expected. 
</P>
</TEXT>
