<HEADLINE> Philippine Stock Exchange to Hold Seminar on Warrants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 26 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine Stock Exchange
(PSE) said today that it will hold a seminar on the trading and
management of warrants on August 29 in Pasig city, Metro Manila.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the newly created PSE Training Institute, the
one-day seminar is expected to further develop awareness and
proficiency in the trading of warrants as part of the PSE's
educational program for brokers.
</P>
<P>
As defined, warrants are financial contracts giving the right
but not the obligation to buy or sell specific shares at a fixed
price on or before a specific date.
</P>
<P>
PSE President Jose Luis Yulo is to make opening remarks at the
seminar and discuss with the participants the reason why the local
bourses are initiating the move to make the investors aware of how
warrants are being managed and traded at the exchange.
</P>
<P>
He said that stock exchanges in Southeast Asia are actively
trading warrants as the Philippines is only trading about four
warrants listed at the PSE.
</P>
<P>
The four warrants are being traded to serve only as a bonus to
the initial public offerings, stock rights and private placements,
he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
