<HEADLINE> Pakistan Making Preparations for Census </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan started today its
preparations for the fifth Housing and Population Census to be
conducted from October 18-31 this year, local press reports said.
</P>
<P>
Some 130,000 people will work for the census and they began
today to get training which will be completed by October 7, the
reports quoted official sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
The census will be the fifth one in Pakistan's history. The
last one was conducted in 1981.
</P>
<P>
The forthcoming census will provide data on sex, age, marital
status, nationality, religion, mother tongue, literacy and
education of the entire population living in the country, said the
reports.
</P>
<P>
The present population of Pakistan is about 140 million and its
growth rate is about 2.7 percent, according to official estimates.
</P>
<P>
