<HEADLINE> Two Mountain Hikers Die, One Injured in Alps </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Two mountain hikers, a man and a
woman, slipped from a rock and died this afternoon in the Alpine
region of Alto Adige bordering Austria, the ANSA news agency said.
</P>
<P>
A German woman slipped on a rock and began to slide when a
group of about 10 Germans were hiking in Val Sarentino.
</P>
<P>
An Alto Adige hotel owner, who was with the hikers, tried to
grab the woman but both fell about 200 meters to their deaths.
</P>
<P>
Another accident occurred this afternoon when 59-year-old
German hiker Anneliese Reinarzt fell 50 meters after slipping on a
path near Sesto Pusteria in the same region.
</P>
<P>
Reinarzt survived the accident with an injured spine and was
recovering in hospital in the town of Brunico.
</P>
<P>
Accidents were frequent during this summer's tourist season in
the Alps. More than 50 people have died in northern Italy so far,
ANSA reported.
</P>
<P>
On the Swiss side of the Alps, six more people died over the
weekend, raising the death toll since mid-July to at least 49,
Reuters reported today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
