<HEADLINE> Italy's Tax Burden Lowered to EU Average </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ROME, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Italy has lowered its tax
burden in the past few years to the European Union average,
according to the state accountancy office report for July.
</P>
<P>
In 1996 the tax burden -- taxes as a proportion of GDP -- was
just under the EU average, four points lower than France's and
almost a point lower than that of Germany.
</P>
<P>
Italy once had the lowest tax burden in Europe, but after
1985, it began to rise much faster than taxes of other industrial
countries. In 1993, Italy's tax burden was higher than Germany's
and just under France's.
</P>
<P>
It fell two points between 1993 and 1996, according to figures
of the Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
