<HEADLINE> Chile's Trade Deficit with US Reaches $136 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, August 25 (Xinhua) -- The trade deficit between Chile
and the United States reached 136 million U.S. dollars in the
first seven months of this year, Chile's Central Bank said.
</P>
<P>
But the bank said the accumulated trading balance for the same
period registered a surplus of 657 million dollars, a 200-million
dollar increase over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Imports in July were 1.55 billion dollars, while exports
totaled 1.41 billion dollars, the bank reported.
</P>
<P>
Exports rose by 2.3 percent in July, compared with the same
month in 1996, thanks to the sales of consumption goods and
capital assets.
</P>
<P>
The Central Bank also said the international monetary reserves
increased 101 million dollars for a total amount of 17.58 billion
dollars by August 15. 
</P>
