<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Bankruptcy Filings Continue to Grow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 25 (Xinhua) -- The number of filings for
Bankruptcy in the United States continued to climb for six
quarters in a row, the American Bankruptcy Institute said today.
</P>
<P>
Bankruptcy filings reached 367,168 for the three-month period
that ended on June 30, said the report based on figures of the
Administrative Office of the U.S. Courts.
</P>
<P>
The figure jumped nearly 10 percent over the first quarter of
1997 and by 23.6 percent as compared with the second quarter of
1996.
</P>
<P>
Non-business bankruptcy filings reached an all-time high of
353,177, which represents 96.2 percent of all filings.
</P>
<P>
Business filings for the quarter, which are at the same level
as a year before, increased by 1.2 percent over the first quarter
of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The total number of bankruptcy filings for the first six months
of the year, which stood at 702,241, exceeds the total filings for
all of calendar year of 1989 (679,461). 
</P>
</TEXT>
