<HEADLINE> Thailand's Budget Deficit Reaches 1.2 Billion Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's budget deficit in the
first 10 months of the current fiscal year starting October was 41
billion baht (1.2 billion U.S. dollars), According to the Thai
Finance Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Revenue since last October to the end of July stood at 682.77
billion baht (20.08 billion dollars), while spending was 723.78
billion baht (21.28 billion dollars), the local press reported
today, quoting figures released by the ministry Monday.
</P>
<P>
In July alone, the budget ran a deficit of 19.98 billion baht
(587 million dollars). Income for the period totaled 56.71 billion
baht (1.66 billion dollars), while spending reach 76.69 billion
baht (2.25 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Finance Ministry announced that treasury
reserves as of July totaled 292.59 billion baht (8.6 billion
dollars), excluding 55.89 billion baht (1.6 billion dollars)
earmarked to set up the civil service pension fund.
</P>
<P>
Total debt until the end of July amounted to 815.6 billion baht
(23.9 billion dollars), 86.92 billion baht (2.55 billion dollars)
more than the previous month.  
</P>
</TEXT>
