<HEADLINE> Li Calls for China-ASEAN Financial Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng said
here today that China and countries of the Association of
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) need to strengthen coordination
and cooperation in the financial field.
</P>
<P>
"We should intensify our coordination and cooperation in the
field of finance and step up the exchange of information so as to
ward off international financial speculation," Li told Singaporean
businessmen in a speech.
</P>
<P>
Over the years, many Asian countries and regions, including
China and ASEAN states, have maintained the momentum of rapid
economic growth, he said.
</P>
<P>
"But we are soberly aware that, compared with developed
countries, the economic strength of countries and regions like
ours is still relatively weak and the financial system not
adequate."
</P>
<P>
Therefore, Asian countries and regions are more vulnerable to
the impact of international financial speculation, Li said.
</P>
<P>
"We should seriously draw lessons from previous financial
crises in the world, keep a high degree of vigilance, strengthen
financial regulation and improve the financial system so as to
forestall and reduce financial risks to the minimum," Li said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier is in Singapore for a three-day visit.
</P>
</TEXT>
