<HEADLINE> Seminar on Myanmar's Export Market Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Trainees from Myanmar's five
ministries, the Chamber of Commerce and Industry and private firms
are currently receiving training in export marketing strategies
and management, the New Light of Myanmar newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
The training is being provided by Singaporean instructors at an
11-day seminar jointly organized by Myanmar's Ministry of Commerce
and the Singapore Trade Development Board. The workshop began on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
According official statistics, Myanmar's export in the 1996-97
fiscal year ending March amounted to 5.242 billion Kyats (873.7
million U.S. dollars according to the official exchange rate),
while its import was 11.343 billion Kyats (1.89 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
The exports mainly covered agricultural, forest and marine
products, minerals and gems.  
</P>
