<HEADLINE> Robinson Signs with Suns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Free-agent forward Cliff
Robinson, who spent eight years with the Portland Trail Blazers,
signed a one-year, 1 million U.S. dollars deal Monday with the
Phoenix Suns.
</P>
<P>
Robinson, 30, averaged 15.1 points per game for the Trail
Blazers after leading the club in scoring in each of the two
previous seasons. He was renounced with three others when the
Blazers signed free-agent forward Brian Grant, who had been with
the Sacramento Kings.
</P>
<P>
Well over the salary cap, the Suns offered 2.08 meters Robinson
their 1 million U.S. dollars cap exemption. He made 2.92 million
U.S. dollars last season with Portland and had been pursued by
several teams.
</P>
<P>
Robinson has career averages of 16.2 points, 5.2 rebounds and
1.1 blocks in 644 career games since being chosen in the second
round of the 1989 draft. 
</P>
</TEXT>
