<HEADLINE> Fuel Prices in Thailand Rise Further </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Fuel prices at the Petroleum
Authority of Thailand's filling stations rose by another 15 satang
per liter today, the seventh increase since the baht flotation on
July 2.
</P>
<P>
The latest price hikes reflect higher oil costs spurred by the
weakened baht which has now tumbled to about 34 baht to the U.S.
dollar.
</P>
<P>
The baht stood at about 26 to the dollar before July 2.
</P>
<P>
The new pump prices at the Petroleum Authority of Thailand's
service stations in Bangkok are 10.80 baht per liter for premium
gasoline, 10.33 baht for regular gasoline and 9.56 baht for
high-speed diesel oil.
</P>
<P>
Analysts here said further fuel price rises are likely if the
baht continues its downward path.  
</P>
</TEXT>
