<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Troops Repulse Tamil Rebel Attacks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka government troops
repulsed Tamil rebel mortar attacks on Sunday at Batticaloa Town
in the Eastern province, according to reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
Two soldiers were killed and 15 others were injured during the
fighting. Four civilians were also killed and 13 others injured
when mortars fired by the rebels of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil
Eelam (LTTE) fell into thickly populated areas at Batticaloa town.
</P>
<P>
The troops, who have launched attacks on Puliyankulam in
Northern Province in the past few days, have recaptured the town's
railway station and are expected to retake the town soon.
</P>
<P>
The government troops launched the campaign to recapture the
town in a bid to restore control over the highway that links the
government-held Vavuniya to Kilinochchi further north, a vital
supply route to the North Jaffna Peninsula.  
</P>
</TEXT>
