<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, August 26 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA -- Canada Monday welcomed a favorable World Trade
Organization's (WTO) panel report on the European Union's (EU) ban
on imports of its beef.
</P>
<P>
The report supports Canada's long-standing position that the
import ban imposed by the EU was "not consistent" with its
obligations under the WTO, said Sergio Marchi, Canada's
international trade minister. (Canada-EU-Beef)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- There is no fixed date for U.S. mediator Dennis
Ross to return to the Middle East as Israel has disclosed, the
State Department said Monday.
</P>
<P>
State Department spokesman James Rubin was responding to a
report that Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu had said
Ross intended to travel to the region to follow up on Palestinian
promises to improve security ties with the Jewish state. "Dennis
Ross has made no decision to travel to the region," Rubin
said. (US-Mideast-Trip)
</P>
