<HEADLINE> Thailand, Myanmar to Cooperate on Drugs Suppression </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Cooperation on amphetamine
suppression will be on the top of the agenda of the 15th Regional
Thai-Myanmar Border Committee meeting which is scheduled to open
today, according to the Thai army.
</P>
<P>
Lt. Gen. Thanom Vatcharaput, commander of the Thai Third Army
Region, was quoted by the local press today as saying that the
spread of the drug along the border was a treat to the national
security of both countries.
</P>
<P>
Without Myanmar's cooperation, suppression of illicit drugs
would be difficult, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Other issues to be discussed at the meeting are the opening of
three permanent checkpoints and repatriation of Myanmar refugees.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar's Southeast Army Commander Maj. Gen. Gade Seng and his
delegation has arrived in Chiang Rai, northern Thailand, to attend
the meeting. The Thai side will be represented by senior military
officers from the third and fourth army regions and the governors
of 10 provinces bordering Myanmar.  
</P>
</TEXT>
