<HEADLINE> South China City Stepping Up Port Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, August 26 (Xinhua) -- One of China's eight major
coastal cities, Shenzhen, in Guangdong province, has eight ports
and 100 berths, 26 of which handle ships of more than ten thousand
tons.
</P>
<P>
Container business in the ports has seen rapid development. In
1996, Shenzhen handled 589,000 standard containers, and this year
it is estimated that there will be one million standard containers.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen government put more money into port construction,
and plans for the layout will be issued.
</P>
<P>
Regulations on improving the ports' handling capacity are
planned, according to a Shenzhen government official. Shenzhen
will also simplify checking procedures for port development. The
Tonggu channel will be dug to stimulate development in the west
port area.  
</P>
