<HEADLINE> More Overseas Investment For Northeast China Economic Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, August 26 (Xinhua) -- The economic and technological
development zone in Changchun, the capital of northeast China's
Jilin province, has seen its overseas investment grow to 678
million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The zone had some 1,720 enterprises, including 211
foreign-funded companies by June, and 50 foreign-backed projects
each have more than 10 million in investment and a sales volume of
more than 100 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Four pillar industries in the zone -- automotive parts, grain
processing, fine chemicals, and electronics have been improved.
</P>
<P>
The zone was set up in 1993, and in the past few years has
spent 900 million yuan on roads, telecommunications, heating
systems, water and power supplies, and other infrastructures.
</P>
<P>
It also has preferential policies simplifying business approval
 formalities and has taken measures to encourage overseas
investors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
