<HEADLINE> Northeast China Province Goes Well With Economic Reforms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
province, one of the oldest and largest industrial bases in the
country, has made major progress in industrial reforms, according
to the provincial planning commission, which says that in 1996,
Liaoning achieved notable success in the reform of its old
industrial enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The central government has made it a pioneer in industrial
reforms and of the 100 firms selected by the state to experiment
with a modern enterprise system, 35 are in Liaoning.
</P>
<P>
Its industrial and technological upgrading has been
enhanced. The debt-asset ratio in state enterprises in Shenyang,
Dalian, Anshan, Fushun and Benxi cities has dropped to 61.9
percent from 66.2 percent at the beginning of the year.
</P>
<P>
Last year 19.92 billion yuan was spent on 2,930 projects, 1,838
of which have been completed, and technological upgrading has
added 13.91 billion yuan in fixed assets, 27.78 billion in sales,
and 4.69 billion yuan in pre-tax profits.
</P>
<P>
A third of the large and medium-sized state-owned enterprises
are doing better and ownership has changed hands in 70 percent of
the small state enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The province has added another 100 state companies to the pilot
project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970826.0275 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Making East China Port International Shipping Hub </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Lianyungang, in China's Jiangsu
province, is trying to build itself into an international cargo
hub for the Pacific.
</P>
<P>
It now has 28 berths, 22 of which have a handling capacity of
10,000 tons each, and a combined annual capacity of 22.25 million
tons.
</P>
<P>
In the first seven months of the year, Lianyungang saw its
cargo volume rise to 21,583 containers handled, an eight-fold
increase from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The port is also expecting four new berths with a handling
capacity of over 10,000 tons each.
</P>
<P>
A feasibility study has shown it to be an ideal port with
potential for 50,000-ton or 100,000-ton berths. The expected
completion of a 6,700 m.-long embankment will accelerate the pace
of becoming an international port with annual cargo capacity of
more than 100 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Because it is mid-way along China's east coast, Lianyungang is
important to cargo transport from northern to southern parts of
the country and with countries on the Pacific rim. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970826.0276 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Farmers Go To Work By Bus In East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Farmers don't usually take the
bus to work, but that's what they're doing in the Pudong New Area
of Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Most of farmers there have left the land and found work in
industry nearby, because of the quick urbanization of the Pudong
New Area. But there is still a group who miss the land and the
days of planting vegetables, and who haven't adapted to the new
way of life in new apartments easily.
</P>
<P>
So the Yanqiao Township government leased a piece of land from
neighboring Sunqiao Township as "recreation land" in 1993. and
many farmers have registered to work on the land. The Yanqiao
Township government also purchased a bus for these "new farmers"
to commute.
</P>
<P>
The land has been turned into a vegetable base for Shanghai
residents and the farmers' income has been increasing. Each is
paid 600 yuan per month.
</P>
<P>
One of the farmers, Grandma Wei, is still good at planting
vegetables in her sixties and says, "I think it is a good way to
keep fit, and when I come back to the vegetable field, my problems
go away."
</P>
<P>
Many young farmers have joined their colleagues in planting
vegetables and earn more than those working in factories, because
of their hard work. The phenomenon has also spread to neighboring
townships.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
