<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Stocks Down on Tight Liquidity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 26 (Xinhua) -- The Jakarta Stock Exchange's
composite index fell a record 5.5 percent Monday to close at the
lowest level in one year, amid worry over high interest rates and
tight liquidity, economic analysts here said today.
</P>
<P>
The composite index plunged by 31.748 points Monday to close at
542.647, down from 574.4 last Friday. The index peaked at 742.95
on July 7.
</P>
<P>
Brokers and analysts blamed high interest rates for the slump
in stock prices.
</P>
<P>
Bank Indonesia, the central bank, last week sharply raised
short-term interest rates to squeeze liquidity and shore up the
newly floated rupiah after it breached the 3,000 level against the
U.S. dollar for the first time ever.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the rupiah weakened Monday against the U.S. dollar
to close at 2,712 rupiah, down from 2,700 rupiah last Friday.
</P>
<P>
Experts said the rupiah needs two to three months to stabilize
and would ultimately settle in a band between 2,700 rupiah and
2,800 rupiah to the dollar. At the start of July, the spot price
in Jakarta was 2,450 rupiah.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah fell to an historic low of 3,045 against the dollar
after the central bank floated the rupiah on August 14 in the wake
of sustained speculative attacks on regional currencies.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah started recovering following the central bank's
raising of interest rates last Tuesday. The bank doubled the
short-term interest rates.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970826.0280 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Life Insurance Sector Growing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's largest trade
and financial center, witnessed a sharp increase in life insurance
earnings in the first half of this year, with total premiums
reaching 4.22 billion yuan (500 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The figure represents an 80.3 percent rise on last year's same
period.
</P>
<P>
Life insurance, which takes the largest portion of the local
insurance market, accounts for nearly 64 percent of the city's
total premium income.
</P>
<P>
The total income of Chinese insurance companies for the period
hit 2.72 billion yuan, up 227.7 percent on the 1996 period.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is one of the two Chinese cities permitting overseas
insurers to engage in local business activities. The American
Intl. Group was the first overseas insurer licensed to operate in
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Insurance experts predict the city's life insurance market will
continue to expand for the foreseeable future in line with the
steady growth in the income of local residents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970826.0281 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Incomes Fall Behind Economic Growth in Costa Rica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Pay increases have been lower
than economic growth in Costa Rica during the past 12 years, a
study carried out by the Economy and Finance Consulting Company
said.
</P>
<P>
Wages grew by six percent during the past 12 years, while the
entire economy grew by 56 percent, the consulting firm said.
</P>
<P>
The study showed the gap between the rich and poor in the
country has widened.
</P>
<P>
In the same time, employment rose by 42 percent, showing that
the Costa Rican economy had favored job-creation over pay
increases.
</P>
<P>
Unemployment remains relatively low in the country, slightly
above six percent, and research shows the average income in the
public sector is higher than that in the private one.
</P>
<P>
During the first half of this year, the average income in the
private sector was 53,000 colones (about 225 U.S. dollars) a
month, while it reached 108,000 colones (about 457 dollars) in
public departments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970826.0282 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nilsson to Play for Sweden for World Cup Match </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Defender Roland Nilsson on
Monday was recalled by Sweden's manager Tommy Svensson for two
World Cup qualifiers which will be key for the Sweden squad to
move into enter next year's finals in France.
</P>
<P>
Sweden will visit Austria on September 6 in a group four match
when it should win to grab a realistic chance of qualifying for
the finals. Four days later the squad hosts Latvia in its
penultimate game in the group.
</P>
<P>
Sweden, who lost home qualifying match to Austria 0-1 last
October, is third in the group with 15 points, one behind Austria
with both teams having played seven matches. Scotland is top with
17 points but has played one more game.
</P>
<P>
Svensson named a 20-man squad which included five home league
players and 15 playing in other European countries.
</P>
<P>
Nilsson, who plays for England premier league Coventry, returns
after a knee injury in place of Helsingborg's Anders Jacobsson.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
