<DOCNO> XIE19970826.0283 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South China Province's Urbanization in Progress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 26 (Xinhua) -- In describing the progress in
Guangdong province in a speech at a recent provincial meeting on
urbanization in rural areas, Tang Bingquan, the deputy governor,
said that there were 1,400 towns in the province by the end of
1996.
</P>
<P>
There is a combined floor space of 1.16 billion sq.m. of
residential housing in these towns, half of which are multi-story
buildings. Per capita living space is 13.4 sq.m.
</P>
<P>
The towns have more than 100,000 km of highways, and
electricity supply, tap water, and computer-controlled telephone
service.
</P>
<P>
Support facilities like schools, hospitals, hospices,
kindergartens, theaters, cinemas, gymnasiums, and hotels have been
built in many of the new towns. Four towns were listed as
national models by the Ministry of Construction last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
