<HEADLINE> Southwest China Region Investing Heavily in Infrastructure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region has put some 180 billion yuan into
infrastructure construction and basic industries in the past
several years.
</P>
<P>
The region has seen its GDP ranking move to 15th place
nationally from 20th in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi has worked out a way to harness and dredge the Xijiang
River, build two local railway lines, build airports in Guilin,
Wuzhou and Liuzhou, expand or rebuild four ports, and build five
highways in keeping with the central government's decision of 1992
to build Guangxi into a corridor to the sea for the Southwest.
</P>
<P>
With improved infrastructure, especially transportation, the
remote autonomous region has seen investment grow in cities on the
Beibu Gulf.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
