<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spanish Soccer Players to Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Spain's Soccer Players
Association (AFE) voted to call a strike on Monday against too
many foreign players in Spanish soccer league, according to state
television.
</P>
<P>
Pedro Antonio Martin, Spain's Sports Secretary, would have a
talk with the AFE on Tuesday, trying to persuade to change the
vote, the television said.
</P>
<P>
More and more people are concerning of glooming Spain's
talented junior players, who are not getting enough time to play
at top level.
</P>
<P>
The Professional Soccer League and the Spanish Soccer
Federation last month made a deal to restrict the number of
"foreign" players to six on each team squad with four allowed on
the pitch at any one time. But such deal did not satisfy the local
players who believed the deal did not go far enough.
</P>
<P>
The first day's action of the season starts on Sunday, which
will not be affected by the strike because there is a legal
waiting period of five days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
