<HEADLINE> China's Investment in Tertiary Industry on Rapid Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 26 (Xinhua) -- China invested 286.6 billion
yuan in the tertiary industry during the first six months of this
year, up 11.2 percent over the same period in 1996, according to
the latest statistics from the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
During the January-June period, China invested 92.1 billion
yuan in transportation, postal and telecommunications services, up
14.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The investment in real estate management, public, residential
and consultancy services hit 122.8 billion yuan, up 5.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
That in commerce, food service, material supply, and marketing
and warehousing was 157.29 billion yuan, up 22.5 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
