<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 26 (Xinhua) -- China's retail sales of social
consumer goods hit 1.3 trillion yuan in the first six months this
year, up 14.1 percent over the same period in 1996, according to
the latest statistics from the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The top three buyers were Guangdong, Jiangsu and Shandong
provinces, and the figures hit 139.1 billion yuan, 104.6 billion
yuan and 92.1 billion yuan, respectively.  
