<HEADLINE> China's Retail Prices Remain Stable in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 26 (Xinhua) -- China's retail price index stood
at 100.8 last June, if the comparable figure of the same period in
1996 is taken as 100, according to the latest statistics from the
State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The biggest price hikes emerged on books, newspapers and
magazines, with the price index hitting 114.1.
</P>
<P>
The prices of fuel and catering services also undertook a
big-margin increase, with their price index jumping to 107.3 and
105.2.  
