<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 26 (Xinhua) -- China's consumer price index
stood at 102.8 last June, if the figure for the same period of
1996 is taken as 100, according to the latest statistics from the
State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The index reached 103.1 in urban areas, and 102.5 in the
countryside, the statistics show.
