<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Italy Get One Gold Each </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 25 (Xinhua) -- China and hosts Italy got
one more gold each on Monday at the on-going World University Games.
</P>
<P>
China's gold came from Lu Haisong who won the women's one-meter
springboard title on the opening day of the diving tournament at
Messina.
</P>
<P>
Italy claimed their first fencing gold through Olympic silver
medalist Valentina Vezzali in the women's individual foil event.
</P>
<P>
Lu, whose best result was a sixth place position at China's
national champions cup, got five high scores in a row in the final to
beat her teammate Chen Lixia for the title.
</P>
<P>
Lu's winning total of 275.16 points is 8.31 points more than Chen,
who caught a cold in the morning but still managed to finish the final
with a fever.
</P>
<P>
Michelle Rojohn of the United States took the bronze medal with a
total of 265.80 points from five dives of the final.
</P>
<P>
In the evening's fencing competitions, Italy got their first gold
of the sport through Olympic silver medalist Valentina Vezzali.
</P>
<P>
Vezzali entered the final after beating Xiao Aihua 15-13 in the
semi-finals. The third period of the match ended when Vezzali led
Xiao 12-10 and Vezzali was awarded a 15-13 victory.
</P>
<P>
Vezzali, who ranks first in the world this year, had an easily job
in the final as she beat her fellow Italian Anna Giacometti 15-9.
</P>
<P>
Xiao Aihua and Ildiko Mincza of Hungary, who lost to Giacometti in
the other semi-final match, tied for the bronze medal of the event.
</P>
<P>
The quarter-finals of the women's volleyball ended on Monday with
the American team beat their Chinese counterparts 3-1. The set scores
were 15-9, 15-8, 2-15, 15-5 in favor of the Americans.
</P>
<P>
In other quarter-final matches, Japan beat Chinese Taipei 3-1 and
Russia downed Switzerland 3-1.
</P>
<P>
In the women's basketball quarter-finals, Italy beat Portugal 57-45
(halftime 24-25) while Cuba trounced Lithuania 95-58. The Cuban team
led the first half 54-27.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, the athletics and swimming tournaments of the
Universiade will begin at Catania and Messina respectively.
</P>
<P>
The semi-finals of the soccer tournament will be played at Palermo
while the men's foil team competitions will be held at Catania and the
men's one-meter springboard diving will be staged at Messina on
Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
