<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New York Stocks Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 25 (Xinhua) -- New York stocks were mixed
today, with smaller-company shares outperforming the blue-chip
sector in an unusually calm session.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average was up as much as 56 points
during the session, but it dropped 28.34 points to 7,859.57.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by nearly a 4-to-3
margin on the New York Stock Exchange, with its volume declining
to just 388.96 million shares, the first full session with a tally
below 400 million since May.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list fell 3.38 to 920.16, and
the NYSE composite index fell 0.90 to 478.03.
</P>
<P>
But the Nasdaq composite index rose 2.84 to 1,601.53, and the
American Stock Exchange composite index rose 3.02 to 646.85. Both
measures are characterized by large numbers of smaller-company
stocks. Likewise, the Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose
2.36 to 418.09.
</P>
<P>
The markets were particularly volatile over the past two weeks.
After gaining more than 100 points in each of the first three
sessions last week, the Dow dropped 127 points on Thursday and
then plunged another 177 points on Friday before rising back in
the final minutes of trading, ending the day down just 6 points.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
