<HEADLINE> FISU Increases Four New Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Georgia, Slovenia, Malawi and
Mozambique have become new members of the International University
Sports Federation (FISU), according to a press release of the
Federation.
</P>
<P>
In an earlier meeting held in Palermo, Sicily island of Italy, the
FISU voted the admission of the four new members. This has brought
the general FISU numbers to 113. 
